179
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:12,620
Thankfully, the young master stepped out and saved us.

180
00:16:14,070 --> 00:16:17,980
Young Lady, you clearly know the man.

181
00:16:17,980 --> 00:16:20,990
Why did you pretend not to know each other?

182
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:25,570
There are things that we don't want to make public.

183
00:16:25,570 --> 00:16:29,350
Is it because you are worried that someone might notice?

184
00:16:29,350 --> 00:16:31,510
You are engaged.

185
00:16:31,510 --> 00:16:34,070
And you don't want people to think you are involved with another man?

186
00:16:34,070 --> 00:16:37,680
He's not a bad person. Don't overthink this.

187
00:16:37,690 --> 00:16:39,360
Young Lady,

188
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:42,430
Do you like him?

189
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:46,390
Why?

190
00:16:46,390 --> 00:16:48,190
Then I don't understand.

191
00:16:48,190 --> 00:16:49,520
If you don't like him,

192
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:51,990
It's hard to figure out his whereabouts. He's not very likable.

193
00:16:51,990 --> 00:16:54,590
Yet you tried protecting him, saying that he is not a bad person.

194
00:16:54,590 --> 00:16:57,920
Why would you protect him if you don't like him?

195
00:17:05,620 --> 00:17:08,500
Protecting him doesn't mean that I like him.

196
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:11,110
It could be out of respect.

197
00:17:11,110 --> 00:17:13,020
What's the difference?

198
00:17:14,140 --> 00:17:19,550
For example, I developed a bad opinion for the Nings because they withdrew from the marriage contract.

199
00:17:19,550 --> 00:17:21,290
Including Young Master Ning.

200
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:24,460
However, by accident,

201
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:28,440
We played chess together without knowing each other's identity.

202
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:31,250
I changed my opinion about him and his way of chess.

203
00:17:31,250 --> 00:17:34,650
